  "body": "# Problem\n\nWe have a few issues that need fixing in the v1 notification screen:\n\n1) Any instance of `seed phrase` must be changed to `recovery phase`.\n2) The red background warning about phrase backup is easy to miss on small screens.\n3) We need to point the links on the page to the right URLs.\n\n[Figma link](https://www.figma.com/file/dEIljL7UPbXgsZUA0Q4qlE5E/Onboarding?node-id=2591%3A22548)\n\n## Implementation\n\n- Update spacing between image & header \n- Update copy in top paragraph (awaiting changes in Figma):\n`Status is taking important steps toward a more secure, censorship resistant network. Thanks for being part of beta; we're sure you'll love v1.0!`\n- Route `Learn more` to a link redirect that can be pointed at the blog post when ready. With help from @jakubgs \n- Link `#status` to https://get.status.im/chat/public/status\n- Link `Twtitter` to https://twitter.com/ethstatus\n- Warning text in the red box says `recovery phrase` rather than `seed phrase`.\n- Move `Got it` button to bottom of page, rather than leaving it fixed on screen, to increase odds of people seeing the full text. \n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- Less spacing at top of screen\n- Copy reads the following at top:\n`Status is taking important steps toward a more secure, censorship resistant network. Thanks for being part of beta; we're sure you'll love v1.0!`\n- Links work.\n- Warning text in the red box says `recovery phrase` rather than `seed phrase`.\n- `Got it` button is below the scroll, not fixed.\n\n## Notes\n\nThe blog post won't be published until next week. Can start draft to use as a placeholder today.",
